    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Moran</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                            Fish</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-08-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi>
                                15, 1871.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Granville promptly instructed British minister to act with Mr. Marsh, and his
                        lordship has received information that the two ministers have already acted
                        on their similar instructions, and requested the consent of the Italian
                        government to the selection of Count Corti as third commissioner. </p>
            </div>
        </body>
